      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIG TIME CHARLIE (2) made it back-to-back wins last start when dictating from the front and proving too quick when the sprint went on. He can find the front again today from the inside draw and repeat the dose as he has done his past couple. SURE INTENTIONS (3) is building nicely this time in, finishing 1.3L off the winner last start at Moruya. The form out of that race has been solid and McDougall takes over from the apprentice hoop. Can raise the bar again getting out to this trip for the first time. CHEBICI (5) finished off strongly last week at Wagga, beaten 1.2L. Likely to get back from the draw again but she rates highly on the back of that effort and another forward showing is on the cards. SOLICITING (8) can improve on the fresh run at Queanbeyan.  ZOUWASE (10) is next best.",
